Description:
    Generates migration to create jobs table (jobs queue).
    Creates example daemon which sequentially runs jobs from queue.
    
    You also need the daemon_generator plugin installed,
    and have invoked: "./script/generate daemon background"
    to create necessary daemon files (see daemon_generator docs).

Quick start:
    ./script/generate daemon background
    ./script/generate background
    rake db:migrate
    ./script/daemons start
    
    then try in console:
    
    job_id = Background.jobs.create(ExampleWorker, :add, 1, 2).id
    
    ...  and after few seconds when background daemon completes the job ...
    
    Background.jobs.find(job_id).result should equal 3

Example:
    ./script/generate background

    This will create:
        db/migrate/xxx_create_jobs.rb
        lib/workers/example_worker.rb
        lib/daemons/background.rb
